review_blob: Bottle. Bozeman, MT. Small malty aroma. Dark brown w diminishing beige head.  Malty balanced bitterness. Some coffee/chocolate notes.  I get a subtle sour, slightly fishy tang at the end. Curious. Nice mild porter.
I think sickassmick pretty much sums it up for me.  The irony of the name pretty much sums it up.

Bottle. Bozeman, MT.  copper brown color. Small sweetish aroma. carmelly crystal malt type body with little hop bitterness. Nice steady body and mouthfeel. Drinkable but nothing remarkable, fits in nicely with Madisons line of unremarkable beers.
beer_name: Madison River Copper John Scotch Ale
